[Patient] What kind of exercise do you recommend for managing my heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Walking or swimming are great options. They are gentle on the heart and improve circulation.
[Patient] How often should I exercise?
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of exercise most days of the week for best results.
[Patient] Are there any exercises I should avoid?
[Healthcare Educator] Avoid high-intensity workouts. Stick to low-impact activities to protect your heart.
[Patient] Can I do strength training exercises?
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, but start with light weights and focus on proper form to avoid straining your heart.
[Patient] How can I stay motivated to exercise regularly?
[Healthcare Educator] Find activities you enjoy, set achievable goals, and consider exercising with a friend for support.